{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月十四|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 14일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 14''' is the 14th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . == Events == * {{ill|Tenpyō-hōji|ja|Tenpyō-hōji|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 8th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|764|ja|764|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 11|ja|11月11日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – Emperor {{ill|Junnin|ja|淳仁天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} (the deposed emperor) was exiled to Awaji. * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1720|ja|1720|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 13|ja|11月13日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – Paper merchant Jiyobei and Kii merchant Koharu committed double suicide; later dramatized by {{ill|Chikamatsu Monzaemon|ja|近松門左衛門|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} in "Shin-chū Tenmōjima". * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1867|ja|1867|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 9|ja|11月9日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The Taisei Hōkan (return of political power) took place as {{ill|Tokugawa Yoshinobu|ja|徳川慶喜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} submitted a memorandum to the court.
== Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1835|ja|1835|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 3|ja|12月3日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Komatsu Seiren|ja|小松清廉|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , a Satsuma retainer and politician († {{ill|1870|ja|1870|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1857|ja|1857|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 30|ja|11月30日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Rikugyaku Nan|ja|陸羯南|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , a political critic and journalist († {{ill|1907|ja|1907|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1865|ja|1865|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Ikamasa Hisaya|ja|岩崎久弥|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , an entrepreneur and 3rd head of the Mitsubishi zaibatsu († {{ill|1955|ja|1955|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1865|ja|1865|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Takegoshi Yosaburō|ja|竹越與三郎|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , a member of the House of Representatives and member of the House of Peers, historian and critic († {{ill|1950|ja|1950|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
